title: For Sale:  SCAR 17 Scam
postcontent:
This listing:
http://www.armslist.com/posts/3204419/kansas-rifles-for-sale--fnh-scar-17

seems to be a scam as it is the SAME EXACT pictures and SAME EXACT text as this gunbroker ad:
http://www.gunbroker.com/Auction/ViewItem.aspx?Item=421152752

I doubt a rifle that sold for $3,100 4 days ago is now being sold for $1,500.


Three easy ways to reduce the number of scams you come across (not a guarentee mind you):
1)  Google image search the included pictures.  Google can show you if they exist elsewhere on the internet.
2)  Google text serach the description.
3)  Ask for a photo of the item with random household items or a piece of paper with a specific word on it.

This just ensures the seller HAS the item not that they will ship it to you.  Consider asking them to ship it through a local FFL near them that YOU pick.  If you pick up the cost of the extra FFL getting involved there should be no hassle.  The FFL can hold it, and once they verify that they have it you can send payment.  

Good luck out there.

title: For Sale:  Glock GSSF Certificate
postcontent:
I have a GSSF Glock Certificate that is valid until 2/27/15. 

The certificate is exchangeable for any Gen 3 Glock G17-G19-G22-G23-G26-G27-G31-G32-G33. 

You simply take the certificate to your local FFL dealer and he mails it plus a copy of his FFL certificate to Glock. Usually within a couple of weeks or so, Glock sends the pistol to your FFL guy and you go pick up your pistol.

There is no charge for shipping and no taxes are due unless you upgrade the certificate. Then, your local sales tax must be added to the upgrade charge ONLY, i.e., you pay taxes on the $35 dollar upgrade ONLY, $35 x .0675 (my state taxes) = $2.36 = $37.36 (total upgrade charge). 

The certificate is upgradeable to the Gen 4 Glocks (same models as previously listed) for an additional charge of $35. 

The certificate can be upgraded the the Gen 3 G37-G38-G39 models (these are the GAP 45 Glocks) for an additional charge of $21.

The certificate can be upgraded for the Gen 3 Glock G20SF-G21SF-G29-G30S-G30SF-G36 for an additional charge of $66.

The certificate can be upgraded to the “Tactical Practical’ competition pistols, the Gen 3 G34 or G35 for an additional $107.

There are other upgrade options but I have listed the most popular upgrades.

Contact me for more information. 

I am asking $450 firm which includes priority shipping.
